oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of 1st Class Machinist Robert Jackson, Supply Co., 114th FA
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Robert Jackson was born in DeKalb County, Tennessee but moved to Wilson County. Jackson served in the Supply Co., 114th FA, 30th Div. earning the rank of 1st Class Machinist. He took part in the St. Mihiel Offensive and the Meuse-Argonne Offensive. He listed is occupation as farmer upon his enlistment and returned to Wilson County after the war.
